<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="165.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,439,464]" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2002" box="[689,870,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inconspicuus">
<emphasis box="[689,870,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">A. inconspicuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the antennal flagellomeres short; the mandible with the lower tooth longer than the others; the clypeus rounded and short, and with the clypeal carina higher than frons level; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the ocelli large; the mesopleural fovea opened; the paramere with the apex rounded; the basiparamere excavated; the basivolsella with an apical excavation at inner margin; and the aedeagus with the apical portion slender, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2002" box="[781,962,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inconspicuus">
<emphasis box="[781,962,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">A. inconspicuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the antennal flagellomeres long; the mandible with with the teeth equally wide; the clypeus angulate and long, with the clypeal carina lower than frons level; the antennal scrobe carinate, but weak; the ocelli small; the mesopleural fovea closed; the basiparamere uniform; the paramere with the apex truncate; the basivolsella straight; and the aedeagus with the apical portion wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
